From 3e3a17d692913e8c5b578be7304b227248ae55fc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 22:56:29 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 166/309] net: stmmac: dwmac-tc956x: Read MAC address from
 firmware

The TC956x wrapper builds the stmmac_resources structure directly and
therefore does not go through devm_stmmac_probe_config_dt(), where most
stmmac platform drivers read the MAC address from device tree.

Read the MAC address with device_get_mac_address() before registering the
stmmac device, and pass it through res.mac. This supports the standard
firmware properties as well as an NVMEM cell named "mac-address".

Only defer probe on -EPROBE_DEFER; otherwise keep the existing stmmac
fallback behavior.

Signed-off-by: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c
index 34b8e3fe1..fbe1fc9e7 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/stmicro/stmmac/dwmac-tc956x.c
@@ -10,6 +10,7 @@
 
 #include <linux/auxiliary_bus.h>
 #include <linux/bitops.h>
+#include <linux/etherdevice.h>
 #include <linux/iopoll.h>
 #include <linux/irqdomain.h>
 #include <linux/irqchip/chained_irq.h>
@@ -745,6 +746,10 @@ static int tc956x_dwmac_probe(struct auxiliary_device *adev,
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, ret,
 				     "failed to initialize stmmac resources\n");
 
+	ret = device_get_mac_address(dev, res.mac);
+	if (ret == -EPROBE_DEFER)
+		return dev_err_probe(dev, ret, "failed to get MAC address\n");
+
 	ret = tc956x_mac_enable(td);
 	if (ret)
 		return dev_err_probe(dev, ret, "failed to enable MAC\n");
